WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:16.720 --> 01:18.324
(BOY PANTING)

01:18.840 --> 01:20.330
(BELLS JINGLING)

01:28.200 --> 01:30.043
Not so fast, Mommy.

01:32.200 --> 01:34.009
Ivan, come on. There's a car coming.

01:39.880 --> 01:41.769
Hi. Do you own this van?

01:42.360 --> 01:43.300
MAN: Yes.

01:43.400 --> 01:44.740
NANA: Um, Mark Hanniway sent me.

01:44.840 --> 01:47.140
- He said you could give us a ride.
- Mark said that?

01:47.240 --> 01:49.891
- Yeah, to the meeting point at mile 92.
- All right.

01:59.040 --> 02:00.087
(MAN COUGHS)

02:07.480 --> 02:08.970
IVAN: (WHISPERS) It's okay, it's okay.

02:10.400 --> 02:11.811
It's just me.

02:21.560 --> 02:22.891
MAN: Here we are.

02:30.440 --> 02:34.300
Um, look for a white Hino
with Wisconsin plates and a plow hookup.

02:34.400 --> 02:35.420
- He's a buddy of mine.
- NANA: Okay.

02:35.520 --> 02:36.860
Sorry, sorry,
I can't take you back myself.

02:36.960 --> 02:38.260
Oh, that's fine. Thanks for the ride.

02:38.360 --> 02:39.780
- No charge.
- Gully, we're here.

02:39.880 --> 02:41.086
Come on, wake up.

02:42.640 --> 02:43.900
MAN: You okay, buddy?

02:44.000 --> 02:45.411
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

02:48.200 --> 02:51.220
Mom, can I go fly Inti?

02:51.320 --> 02:52.606
NANA: Just wait, okay?

02:53.280 --> 02:55.851
First, I got to figure out
what all this is.

02:58.160 --> 02:59.605
Let's go, Ivan.

03:16.600 --> 03:19.570
(WHISPERS) Gully, Gully, look.
Look over there.

03:20.760 --> 03:22.125
(MAN WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY)

03:27.840 --> 03:29.126
That's Architect Newman.

03:33.800 --> 03:35.500
What's he giving them?

03:35.600 --> 03:36.860
WOMAN: Turns.

03:36.960 --> 03:38.610
It's just luck of the draw.

03:41.480 --> 03:42.606
Thank you.

03:45.840 --> 03:47.300
- Thank you.
- It's your turn, honey.

03:47.400 --> 03:49.500
- Put your hand out.
- Can I have two?

03:49.600 --> 03:51.700
One for me and one for my brother?

03:51.800 --> 03:53.020
And where's your brother?

03:53.120 --> 03:56.500
Your brother doesn't need it, honey.
Only you get one.

03:56.600 --> 03:59.080
First pebble up is the white one.
Don't forget, now.

03:59.640 --> 04:02.166
MAN: Thank you. Thank you so much.

04:03.680 --> 04:05.380
(INTI SCREECHING)

04:05.480 --> 04:06.641
(BELLS JINGLING)

04:25.400 --> 04:27.687
You can unwrap your pebbles now.

04:39.160 --> 04:41.640
GULLY: Mommy, we got green.

04:43.360 --> 04:45.980
(SNIFFLES) It's no biggie.

04:46.080 --> 04:48.924
WOMAN: Here. We've got the white one.

04:49.040 --> 04:51.042
(PEOPLE MURMURING INDISTINCTLY)

04:56.920 --> 04:59.100
- NEWMAN: What's your name?
- Timothy.

04:59.200 --> 05:00.380
WOMAN: Can I go in with him?

05:00.480 --> 05:02.164
NEWMAN: Only the one who needs healing.

05:02.280 --> 05:03.566
The structure's too fragile.

05:03.840 --> 05:05.660
I'll be in there with him, though.

05:05.760 --> 05:07.762
We'll be buddies, right, Timothy?

05:08.400 --> 05:09.845
Come on, now.

05:19.560 --> 05:21.050
(SCREECHING)

05:25.560 --> 05:26.561
(PEOPLE EXCLAIM)

05:27.880 --> 05:30.850
Excuse me. Excuse me.

05:31.040 --> 05:32.980
- Mommy!
- Gully, Gully, wait here.

05:33.080 --> 05:34.540
- Will you watch my son?
- WOMAN: What are you doing?

05:34.640 --> 05:37.580
- It's my boy's falcon.
- You can't go in there.

05:37.680 --> 05:40.081
- Gully, don't move. Stay there.
- WOMAN: It's forbidden!

05:41.160 --> 05:43.606
- WOMAN 2: Hey!
- MAN: Don't go in there!

05:45.720 --> 05:47.290
- NANA: It's my boy's falcon.
- NEWMAN: Shh.

05:48.600 --> 05:49.740
NANA: I can get him out.

05:49.840 --> 05:51.888
NEWMAN: I'll get him to
fly out the way he came in.

05:54.360 --> 05:55.361
(BELLS JINGLING)

05:57.120 --> 05:58.121
(SCREECHING)

05:59.200 --> 06:00.440
(BRANCHES RUSTLING)

06:04.840 --> 06:06.180
He's flying to the light.

06:06.280 --> 06:08.169
(SCREECHING CONTINUES)

06:22.120 --> 06:23.326
(NANA GRUNTS)

06:33.080 --> 06:34.684
NANA: (WHISPERS) Don't be scared.

06:36.760 --> 06:38.330
Look.

06:55.080 --> 06:56.684
NEWMAN: We're done here.

06:59.840 --> 07:00.841
(PEOPLE MURMURING INDISTINCTLY)

07:01.160 --> 07:02.605
Mommy?

07:05.000 --> 07:06.365
Where's Inti?

07:06.680 --> 07:08.340
- WOMAN: Are you hurt?
- TIMOTHY: No.

07:08.440 --> 07:10.249
WOMAN: No? What happened in there?

07:10.680 --> 07:12.648
MAN: Hey, lady! Lady!

07:13.360 --> 07:14.900
Are there no more healings, then?

07:15.000 --> 07:16.684
What, do you have to leave now?

07:26.680 --> 07:31.402
MAN: Longley, Kjellberg,
Lyrenmann and Walker.

07:33.960 --> 07:35.620
You can't leave us stranded here.
Come on.

07:35.720 --> 07:36.820
I'm sorry, ma'am,

07:36.920 --> 07:40.540
but I was told you and your kids, fine,
but the hawk, no way.

07:40.640 --> 07:42.940
The man couldn't have been any clearer.

07:43.040 --> 07:45.700
NANA: Well, the man could
have the guts to say it to my face.

07:45.800 --> 07:47.940
I could, but I don't care to.

07:48.040 --> 07:51.500
You don't care to empathize?
Everyone's gone.

07:51.600 --> 07:53.740
What am I supposed to do?
They're little kids.

07:53.840 --> 07:55.500
Oh, save the theatrics, lady.

07:55.600 --> 07:57.860
You know, you're not the only one

07:57.960 --> 08:00.020
who knows what it's like
at the end of the tether.

08:00.120 --> 08:02.771
We all do, or else we wouldn't be here.

08:04.240 --> 08:07.403
My whole life,
listening to begging and crying,

08:08.160 --> 08:10.060
and not able to do
a goddamn thing about it.

08:10.160 --> 08:12.367
So don't expect any coddling.

08:13.240 --> 08:17.060
Piece-of-shit bird should've gone down
with the structure, all due respect.

08:17.160 --> 08:20.721
Just let the boy walk home with it.
At least that option's open to him.

08:31.160 --> 08:33.481
LANCE: Jeff, come on,
let's move, it's getting dark.

08:35.760 --> 08:38.923
MAN: Sorry, lady. The hawk or your kids.

08:39.799 --> 08:41.659
WOMAN: Who would bring that bird here?

08:41.760 --> 08:43.489
NANA: How about you shut your mouth.

08:43.760 --> 08:47.890
IVAN: Fine! I'll walk.
I don't care. I'm not leaving Inti.

08:49.880 --> 08:51.120
Ivan...

08:52.240 --> 08:54.607
We can't. We'll freeze, baby.

08:55.000 --> 08:57.700
Why did you have to make me come with?
It's all Gully's fault.

08:57.800 --> 08:59.325
NANA: It's no one's fault, honey.

08:59.800 --> 09:01.404
Look.

09:01.760 --> 09:03.489
Inti's a big boy, right?

09:04.000 --> 09:06.162
Let him fly, he'll follow us home.

09:06.840 --> 09:08.808
Do as I say. Now.

09:10.000 --> 09:11.809
(ENGINE STARTING)

09:21.320 --> 09:22.651
Good-bye.

09:29.960 --> 09:30.961
(IVAN EXCLAIMS)

09:31.600 --> 09:33.045
No!

09:33.320 --> 09:35.163
NANA: What is the matter with you?

09:35.840 --> 09:37.900
- Are you insane?
- MAN: What in the world?

09:38.000 --> 09:39.740
NANA: Are you insane?

09:39.840 --> 09:41.620
Now we're even.

09:41.720 --> 09:43.180
Ivan?

09:43.280 --> 09:45.169
Ivan, come back!

09:52.160 --> 09:53.340
(JANIA SPEAKING FRENCH)

09:53.440 --> 09:55.727
Well, I should get there soon.

09:55.840 --> 09:56.940
Luckily I had the GPS.

09:57.040 --> 09:58.020
(GARREL SPEAKING FRENCH ON PHONE)

09:58.120 --> 09:59.087
How is it?

09:59.200 --> 10:00.180
(JANIA SPEAKING)

10:00.280 --> 10:02.100
Crazy. There's snow everywhere.
It's like driving on the clouds.

10:02.200 --> 10:03.180
(GARREL SPEAKING)

10:03.280 --> 10:06.090
I am glad. You sound well.

10:06.200 --> 10:07.700
(JANIA SPEAKING)

10:07.800 --> 10:11.202
Please help me find
the coordinates for the next act.

10:11.520 --> 10:14.820
If not...
Her son is my last chance to find her.

10:14.920 --> 10:15.900
(GARREL SPEAKING)

10:16.000 --> 10:17.020
I know, I am trying.

10:17.120 --> 10:19.820
I wish you had changed your mind...

10:19.920 --> 10:21.684
I can't help it.

10:22.440 --> 10:25.808
Anyway, everything's fine.

10:26.400 --> 10:28.562
Don't worry, I feel good.

10:32.200 --> 10:34.043
- ALICE: I know, baby.
- (BABY MUMBLING)

10:34.600 --> 10:35.726
Give me that.

10:41.560 --> 10:43.050
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

10:47.920 --> 10:49.660
- JANIA: Hi.
- Yes. Can I help you?

10:49.760 --> 10:51.140
Yeah. I'm Jania Ressemore.

10:51.240 --> 10:53.580
I'm a journalist with La Nationale TV.

10:53.680 --> 10:55.340
And I spoke with Ivan Ephron.

10:55.440 --> 10:57.300
We scheduled an interview for today.

10:57.400 --> 10:59.340
- I don't know anything about anything.
- (BOTTLE CLATTERS)

10:59.440 --> 11:00.820
Oh, shit!

11:00.920 --> 11:02.660
I'm sorry. Yes, I forgot.

11:02.760 --> 11:05.540
Oh, hang on. Baby, what the...

11:05.640 --> 11:08.260
Stay over there, okay?
Thank you. Uh, that's fine.

11:08.360 --> 11:12.500
Um, Ivan's out back in the red cabin.

11:12.600 --> 11:14.100
- Thank you.
- Sorry.

11:14.200 --> 11:15.500
So, I'm going?

11:15.600 --> 11:16.940
- Just, yeah, just around the corner.
- Okay.

11:17.040 --> 11:18.530
- If you don't mind.
- Thank you. Thanks.

11:19.320 --> 11:21.687
- (BABY MUMBLING)
- Baby, what's this?

11:22.160 --> 11:23.161
(DOOR CLOSING)

11:29.800 --> 11:31.484
(DISTANT RATTLING)

11:51.600 --> 11:53.125
- (WINGS FLUTTERING)
- (BELLS JINGLING)

11:57.600 --> 12:01.082
IVAN: (SOFTLY) It's okay. It's okay.

12:02.680 --> 12:04.500
It's okay.

12:04.600 --> 12:06.220
(FALCON SCREECHING)

12:06.320 --> 12:07.890
It's okay.

12:09.360 --> 12:11.806
It's okay. It's okay.

12:13.520 --> 12:15.329
It's okay.

12:15.880 --> 12:17.928
Hey, it's okay.

12:18.840 --> 12:20.524
It's just me.

12:21.240 --> 12:22.287
(FALCON SCREECHES)

12:27.800 --> 12:29.040
IVAN: Oh.

12:34.280 --> 12:35.770
JANIA: I'm sorry.

12:36.480 --> 12:37.641
Who the fuck are you?

12:38.080 --> 12:39.844
I'm Jania Ressemore.

12:42.880 --> 12:44.220
We...

12:44.320 --> 12:46.322
We spoke over the phone
a few weeks back.

12:47.160 --> 12:50.289
We scheduled an interview for today,
and, uh...

12:51.040 --> 12:54.522
A documentary on hybrid falcons.

13:02.840 --> 13:04.490
(CLEARS THROAT) How did you get in here?

13:05.080 --> 13:07.731
Oh, it's your wife.
She told me to come back here.

13:15.240 --> 13:16.860
I can come back tomorrow,
if that's better for you.

13:16.960 --> 13:19.620
No, I just forgot. It's fine.
(CLEARS THROAT)

13:19.720 --> 13:20.846
Okay.

13:23.520 --> 13:26.046
So, you've got the market
on hybrids cornered.

13:27.240 --> 13:29.720
People say your birds
are the most beautiful out there.

13:32.440 --> 13:33.566
They are.

13:35.480 --> 13:37.289
Are you completely self-taught?

13:38.360 --> 13:41.980
Uh, no, I learned from my grandfather.

13:42.080 --> 13:43.445
Oh.

13:45.560 --> 13:47.980
I understand Nana Kunning
is your mother.

13:48.080 --> 13:49.764
Do you two maintain a relationship?

13:51.960 --> 13:54.088
You don't share a last name,
that's why I ask.

14:00.280 --> 14:03.363
It's just a question. You don't have
to answer if you don't want to.

14:05.960 --> 14:07.530
ALICE: I made a fresh pot.

14:15.400 --> 14:16.765
Excuse me.

14:21.160 --> 14:24.220
- Baby, what was that?
- I don't want to talk to her.

14:24.320 --> 14:25.500
- Well, what do you want me to say?
- I don't know.

14:25.600 --> 14:26.860
- I don't care what you say.
- That's very horrible.

14:26.960 --> 14:29.964
IVAN: I do not want to talk to her.

14:32.520 --> 14:33.851
(ALICE CLEARS THROAT)

14:36.240 --> 14:37.526
I'm sorry.

14:40.280 --> 14:42.408
So, I guess we're all done?

14:43.720 --> 14:46.291
Yeah, I think so. I'm sorry about that.

14:47.640 --> 14:48.971
I'll walk you out.

14:49.320 --> 14:51.322
- (BABY CRYING)
- (KISSING)

14:52.000 --> 14:53.729
Aw, baby.

15:06.160 --> 15:07.650
Can you take him?

15:08.160 --> 15:10.003
Come here, buddy. Come here, buddy.

15:10.680 --> 15:13.081
- Hello. Hello.
- (CRYING STOPS)

15:13.440 --> 15:16.842
- (BABY COOING)
- Good boy. Good boy.

15:17.440 --> 15:18.580
Oh...

15:18.680 --> 15:20.205
So, are you gonna tell me what happened?

15:24.480 --> 15:26.100
What? What?

15:26.200 --> 15:27.300
What? Oh...

15:27.400 --> 15:29.050
She left that for you.

15:29.520 --> 15:31.090
- What?
- That.

15:36.080 --> 15:38.082
What? Why did you take this?

15:39.920 --> 15:42.020
Well, you would have said
exactly the same thing if I hadn't.

15:42.120 --> 15:44.420
You absolutely refuse
to mind your own business.

15:44.520 --> 15:47.888
- Huh?
- Oh, yeah, I'm such a nosy, nosy woman.

15:53.040 --> 15:55.168
It's cold. You should put it
in the microwave.

16:00.200 --> 16:01.690
Can you take him?

16:02.720 --> 16:04.404
I've had him all day.

16:05.160 --> 16:06.446
What have we got here?

16:06.720 --> 16:08.563
- Ah-ah.
- (CUTLERY CLATTERING)

16:09.000 --> 16:10.365
Well...

16:34.240 --> 16:35.765
(SIGHS)

16:43.040 --> 16:45.122
(WHISPERS) Alice. Alice.

16:46.600 --> 16:48.090
Alice.

16:48.520 --> 16:49.660
Huh?

16:49.760 --> 16:51.900
- IVAN: It doesn't close.
- ALICE: Yeah, it does.

16:52.000 --> 16:53.411
You have to hold it.

16:53.760 --> 16:56.081
Just put your finger there.
It's an old computer.

16:57.640 --> 17:01.100
I can't believe... There's nobody on earth
who doesn't know how to use a computer.

17:01.200 --> 17:02.611
I swear to God.

17:03.160 --> 17:04.500
(KISSING) Thank you, honey. Thank you.

17:04.599 --> 17:06.602
Don't go playing gentleman on me now.
Come on.

17:17.560 --> 17:18.846
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

17:22.359 --> 17:25.700
WOMAN: (ON VIDEO) I've seen her.
I've followed her work for a long time.

17:25.800 --> 17:27.290
She's amazing.

17:32.280 --> 17:34.328
MAN:
Shh. That's her. That's Nana Kunning.

17:36.320 --> 17:37.481
Shh...

17:53.760 --> 17:55.285
(CLOSES LAPTOP)

17:57.840 --> 18:00.620
It hurts, right? I know. I know.

18:00.720 --> 18:02.051
- I know.
- (SOW SQUEALING)

18:05.520 --> 18:06.931
Hans!

18:09.720 --> 18:11.449
- Shh. Huh-huh.
- (SQUEALING)

18:11.800 --> 18:12.847
Oh!

18:13.960 --> 18:15.166
Hans!

18:15.280 --> 18:17.851
Hans! I need help.

18:18.960 --> 18:20.325
(SHUSHING)

18:25.600 --> 18:26.601
(PIGLET SNORTING)

18:37.400 --> 18:39.607
MAN: Nana? Nana?

18:39.960 --> 18:41.530
There's someone here to see you.

18:45.040 --> 18:46.724
HANS: Hey, Nana?

18:49.000 --> 18:52.561
You're only here three hours a day.
Try not to have any visitors, okay?

19:14.000 --> 19:15.445
How did you get here?

19:16.160 --> 19:17.446
NEWMAN: I walked.

19:19.080 --> 19:20.570
How'd you find me?

19:22.360 --> 19:24.203
- You're looking for me, right?
- Mmm-hmm.

19:24.920 --> 19:26.660
I hope you remember me.

19:26.760 --> 19:28.171
Yeah, you're the Architect.

19:29.600 --> 19:31.602
And you're Alana Ephron.

19:32.120 --> 19:34.248
They said I'd find you here.

19:34.360 --> 19:36.931
I'm Nana. No one calls me Alana.

19:38.200 --> 19:40.248
The boy, Timothy, you remember?

19:42.080 --> 19:43.445
He's better.

19:45.600 --> 19:47.860
The swelling in his eye went down.

19:47.960 --> 19:50.020
Half his vision is back.

19:50.120 --> 19:51.963
Pretty unexpected.

19:53.920 --> 19:56.287
Is this about my son's falcon?

19:57.200 --> 19:59.806
Your son's bird didn't deserve to die,
and I'm sorry.

20:07.040 --> 20:08.405
Congratulations.

20:09.800 --> 20:11.404
On the boy, I mean.

20:13.160 --> 20:14.969
Congratulate yourself.

20:15.600 --> 20:17.125
Myself? Why's that?

20:18.600 --> 20:21.260
It was you who touched
the boy's eyes, not me.

20:21.360 --> 20:23.124
And I had to tell you so.

20:27.840 --> 20:29.171
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

20:32.160 --> 20:33.685
Okay. (CHUCKLES)

20:36.480 --> 20:38.482
I got to go back to work inside.

20:40.880 --> 20:43.281
I appreciate your concern over my son.

20:45.720 --> 20:48.200
I'm glad about the boy. Really.

20:49.360 --> 20:50.850
I am.

20:52.080 --> 20:54.162
If he's really cured, I mean.

20:55.800 --> 20:59.202
Listen, I'll be in town a few more days
if you have any questions.

21:00.840 --> 21:03.320
I'm staying with the boy's family
near the church.

21:04.640 --> 21:05.846
Have a nice day.

21:16.480 --> 21:18.244
DOCTOR: Can you do this one?

21:18.360 --> 21:20.044
Do it as fast as you can. Let's see.

21:21.200 --> 21:24.044
Oh. Okay, that's very good.

21:24.160 --> 21:25.571
Jump. All right.

21:25.680 --> 21:29.300
So, now I want you to walk like a duck.
Can you walk like a duck?

21:29.400 --> 21:31.801
Like this? Without falling over? Hmm?

21:34.000 --> 21:35.220
Yeah.

21:35.320 --> 21:38.460
Wow. Very good, Gully. (CHUCKLING)

21:38.560 --> 21:40.289
You seem to be in pretty good shape.

21:43.080 --> 21:46.129
(SIGHS) Well, for now, we're fine.

21:46.560 --> 21:47.540
Um...

21:47.640 --> 21:51.460
The growth seems to have
just stabilized. It hasn't...

21:51.560 --> 21:53.210
- It's only a minor variation.
- Mmm.

21:54.080 --> 21:55.060
Um...

21:55.160 --> 21:58.846
I feel that he's different.

21:59.240 --> 22:00.480
That, um...

22:01.880 --> 22:04.645
Like he's regressed.

22:04.760 --> 22:06.649
- How do you mean?
- Um...

22:07.720 --> 22:09.340
He wets himself.

22:09.440 --> 22:11.044
He can't control it.

22:11.920 --> 22:15.242
And it doesn't embarrass him, either.
He doesn't even bother to tell me.

22:15.720 --> 22:18.929
Is that related to the tumor?

22:19.560 --> 22:20.891
Possibly.

22:21.880 --> 22:26.124
(SIGHS) If he doesn't notice it,
uh, try not to make a big deal of it.

22:28.480 --> 22:29.970
Have you heard back?

22:31.680 --> 22:34.180
Nana, as I told you before,

22:34.280 --> 22:38.205
it's a very high-risk operation
for what little can possibly be achieved.

22:39.280 --> 22:41.660
I'm afraid there just
haven't been any surgeons

22:41.760 --> 22:43.489
who are willing to take that chance.

22:44.880 --> 22:46.041
I'm sorry.

22:51.360 --> 22:53.180
I know you've been
through this once before.

22:53.280 --> 22:55.282
There must have been
advances since then.

22:58.040 --> 22:59.280
Please?

23:01.200 --> 23:03.020
Okay, look, I will make some more calls.

23:03.120 --> 23:04.340
- Please.
- Okay. All right?

23:04.440 --> 23:05.771
- Okay.
- All right.

23:25.120 --> 23:26.326
NANA: Hey.

23:27.040 --> 23:29.042
What do you say we go do something?

23:31.760 --> 23:33.762
How about we go get cider donuts?

23:36.040 --> 23:37.041
Hmm?

23:40.880 --> 23:42.644
Don't you think
you've punished me enough?

23:47.120 --> 23:50.329
You know life's gonna throw you
heavier punches, right?

23:51.000 --> 23:52.260
It's fine.

23:52.360 --> 23:55.364
You want to, um,
just keep trying to dodge them?

23:56.680 --> 23:59.650
I can't stop that,
but I'm gonna tell you something.

23:59.880 --> 24:01.211
You listening to me?

24:03.840 --> 24:05.683
You will never learn how to hit back.

24:21.280 --> 24:23.044
NANA: I need you boys
to wait here for a minute.

24:23.240 --> 24:24.860
- Okay?
- GULLY: Mommy, I want to go with you.

24:24.960 --> 24:27.566
IVAN: Mom, I hate staying
in the car. I'm sick of it.

24:30.520 --> 24:31.521
(CAR DOOR OPENING)

24:32.880 --> 24:34.609
Ivan, stay in the car.

24:38.360 --> 24:41.170
Ivan, you can't leave your brother.

24:46.920 --> 24:48.331
Okay, fine.

24:49.120 --> 24:50.121
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

25:01.440 --> 25:04.523
NANA: I would've let you know
we were coming, but I didn't plan this.

25:07.240 --> 25:08.241
(INDISTINCT COMMENTARY ON TV)

25:08.440 --> 25:09.930
NEWMAN: It's the playoffs.

25:10.760 --> 25:12.603
Go and watch, if you're interested.

25:12.800 --> 25:13.926
NANA: Okay.

25:15.760 --> 25:17.967
Gully, why don't you go
with your brother?

25:32.280 --> 25:33.964
My little boy's getting worse.

25:35.720 --> 25:37.245
NEWMAN: I'm sorry.

25:38.120 --> 25:39.121
Mmm-hmm.

25:40.240 --> 25:43.528
That's what the doctors say,
but none of them will operate on him.

25:44.600 --> 25:46.807
I wouldn't be here
if I weren't out of options.

25:48.480 --> 25:51.609
No one would.
You think I don't know that?

25:54.600 --> 25:56.443
For what it's worth,
I don't ask for money.

25:57.320 --> 25:59.084
(CLEARS THROAT)
Well, you're staying in their house.

26:00.440 --> 26:02.169
Never refuse an invitation.

26:04.480 --> 26:06.881
Maybe you get off
on other people's weaknesses.

26:10.040 --> 26:13.100
If your agenda is to insult me,

26:13.200 --> 26:16.249
at least send the boys out,
and we can thrash this out in the bedroom.

26:17.160 --> 26:19.527
- (SCOFFS)
- Just a joke.

26:19.640 --> 26:20.926
Fuck.

26:22.040 --> 26:23.849
This is absurd.

26:24.280 --> 26:25.900
Oh, it is.

26:26.000 --> 26:28.890
Maybe it all is, but especially this.

26:31.000 --> 26:32.365
Just look at you.

26:33.720 --> 26:35.688
Here you are, at your wit's end,

26:36.600 --> 26:38.682
still putting up with a man
that you think is a fraud.

26:41.000 --> 26:42.650
Searching me out.

26:44.160 --> 26:45.525
Of course it's absurd.

26:47.520 --> 26:50.046
But I think you're
beginning to see what I already know.

26:52.240 --> 26:54.242
We can't avoid pain.

26:56.120 --> 26:57.246
But resisting it,

26:58.120 --> 27:00.202
- that's what causes all the problems.
- (CLEARS THROAT)

27:00.760 --> 27:02.100
Here's to that.

27:02.200 --> 27:04.726
Right now, everything is
incomprehensible to me.

27:05.720 --> 27:07.529
My little boy hasn't even lived yet.

27:09.480 --> 27:10.811
What was he born for?

27:12.160 --> 27:13.685
To die?

27:17.760 --> 27:19.569
Can you help me or not?

27:20.040 --> 27:22.884
Everyone's eager to receive, Alana.

27:24.920 --> 27:26.460
Giving's different.

27:26.560 --> 27:29.245
It's the harder road.
It's the one for you.

27:29.560 --> 27:31.562
You haven't answered my question.

28:00.800 --> 28:02.211
NANA: Timothy?

28:36.280 --> 28:38.580
WOMAN: No, it's room 12. It's the...

28:38.680 --> 28:40.780
One second.
It's the toilet and the sink, okay?

28:40.880 --> 28:42.882
- Yeah, I need it done. Thanks.
- (TAPPING RHYTHMICALLY)

28:43.760 --> 28:44.740
How can I help you?

28:44.840 --> 28:48.140
Yeah, I'm looking for Jania Ressemore.
I think she's staying at this hotel.

28:48.240 --> 28:50.163
- Do you have a room number?
- No.

28:51.640 --> 28:53.165
(CLEARS THROAT)

28:57.720 --> 28:59.848
You know what, forget it. Forget it.

29:00.040 --> 29:01.020
(JANIA SPEAKING FRENCH)

29:01.120 --> 29:02.121
39? OK.

29:04.240 --> 29:05.844
No, no, this is awesome!

29:07.280 --> 29:09.089
Why did she change her mind?

29:11.160 --> 29:13.162
Thank you.

29:15.440 --> 29:17.100
No, no, I can leave.

29:17.200 --> 29:18.690
I'm done here.

29:20.520 --> 29:21.500
I don't know.

29:21.600 --> 29:24.126
Just confirm, as soon as possible.

29:25.480 --> 29:29.246
66 degrees, 33, 39.

29:30.320 --> 29:31.367
Love, bye.

29:34.040 --> 29:35.451
(IN ENGLISH) What is that?

29:37.360 --> 29:39.681
It was shot in secret
by some of her followers.

29:40.040 --> 29:42.122
Ah, thank you for stating the obvious.

29:44.040 --> 29:47.220
Most of them were taken in '97, '98,

29:47.320 --> 29:49.322
when you were about 18.

29:51.080 --> 29:52.366
Consider it a gift.

29:52.560 --> 29:55.723
I don't usually share my
documentary footage with anyone.

29:58.280 --> 30:03.127
And now someone has hooked you up
for the coordinates for the next act, huh?

30:06.040 --> 30:07.405
I want to go with you.

30:10.640 --> 30:12.244
I don't need you anymore.

30:14.280 --> 30:15.611
No offense.

30:16.120 --> 30:18.282
- (SCOFFS)
- WAITRESS: Excuse me.

30:18.640 --> 30:20.060
- Hi.
- Can I get you a coffee?

30:20.160 --> 30:21.980
Yeah, coffee, please.

30:22.080 --> 30:23.580
Okay, listen.

30:23.680 --> 30:25.648
You came to me

30:25.760 --> 30:29.207
because you think that
I know something about her.

30:30.440 --> 30:31.930
What do you say?

30:33.240 --> 30:35.083
It's above the Arctic Circle.

30:36.040 --> 30:38.980
Hundreds of miles,
some of it over frozen ocean.

30:39.080 --> 30:40.820
You don't want to bother, trust me.

30:40.920 --> 30:44.208
- That's fine. That's totally fine.
- (SIGHS)

30:46.960 --> 30:49.088
(IVAN BREATHING HEAVILY)

30:49.760 --> 30:50.966
(ALICE MOANING)

31:03.280 --> 31:05.169
ALICE: Yeah, yeah.

31:18.520 --> 31:20.648
(IVAN COOING)

31:21.880 --> 31:23.086
(CHUCKLES)

31:23.880 --> 31:25.211
Okay.

31:25.320 --> 31:26.924
- (BABY MUMBLING)
- Mmm.

31:27.320 --> 31:30.961
(WHISPERING)
Okay, bye-bye. Bye-bye, bye-bye.

31:31.240 --> 31:32.220
(WHIMPERS)

31:32.320 --> 31:34.420
What? I'll be back.

31:34.520 --> 31:37.100
I'll call. I'll call you.

31:37.200 --> 31:39.140
And Mommy, okay?

31:39.240 --> 31:40.526
I love you.

31:41.600 --> 31:43.170
(CRYING)

31:50.400 --> 31:51.686
(BELLS JINGLING)

31:58.840 --> 32:00.410
- Bye.
- Bye.

32:02.040 --> 32:03.565
- See you.
- See you.

32:44.080 --> 32:45.570
WOMAN: Your passports?

32:45.880 --> 32:48.900
There's only one gate, so...
And boarding's at 6:30.

32:49.000 --> 32:50.580
- You'll have a bit of a wait.
- Okay.

32:50.680 --> 32:54.366
WOMAN: And arrival in Nunavut
is at approximately 12:30.

32:56.240 --> 32:57.526
JANIA: Here we go.

32:58.160 --> 33:02.140
Uh, I would like to use the time before
takeoff to do the interview, if that's okay.

33:02.240 --> 33:05.369
Yeah, you can record my voice,
but just not me.

33:06.200 --> 33:07.700
But we had an agreement.

33:07.800 --> 33:10.610
Yeah, I agreed.
I agreed to answer your questions.

33:11.080 --> 33:12.525
(JANIA SIGHS)

33:15.480 --> 33:17.209
IVAN: Okay, I'll tell you a story.

33:18.840 --> 33:20.604
Do you know I had a little brother?

33:22.320 --> 33:24.129
We were kids, and, uh...

33:26.280 --> 33:28.203
He wanted a glass of water.

33:29.240 --> 33:31.686
And, uh, he couldn't reach the glass.

33:32.280 --> 33:34.601
So he asked me to get the glass.
I was watching...

33:36.560 --> 33:38.820
I was watching some crap on TV,
and I didn't want to help him.

33:38.920 --> 33:41.127
And he went and he...

33:42.080 --> 33:44.180
He got the glass, and he fell,

33:44.280 --> 33:46.740
and he cut his face,
and he cut his hands, and...

33:46.840 --> 33:48.365
He hit his head.

33:50.600 --> 33:52.100
So they take him to the hospital,

33:52.200 --> 33:55.500
and they do all these tests,

33:55.600 --> 33:57.807
and they find out that he's sick.

33:58.000 --> 33:59.570
The kid is sick.

34:04.160 --> 34:05.605
And...

34:05.960 --> 34:08.485
(CHUCKLES) I just felt relief.

34:10.600 --> 34:11.860
I just felt relief

34:11.960 --> 34:15.980
that it wasn't my fault
for not having helped him.

34:16.080 --> 34:19.880
And I felt relief that it wasn't me
that was sick.

34:22.120 --> 34:23.380
(SIGHS)

34:23.480 --> 34:25.460
And all I know

34:25.560 --> 34:27.766
is that my little brother was sick,

34:28.239 --> 34:29.810
(WHISPERS) and she couldn't heal him.

35:05.160 --> 35:06.321
(TOOTHBRUSH CLATTERS)

35:10.200 --> 35:11.884
(TOILET FLUSHING)

35:25.640 --> 35:28.371
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

35:29.560 --> 35:30.607
(SOBS)

35:32.640 --> 35:33.971
(SNIFFLES)

35:44.720 --> 35:46.290
(SIGHS)

35:52.440 --> 35:54.090
So what about you, Ressemore?

35:54.400 --> 35:57.165
You got any kids? You got a husband?

35:59.240 --> 36:00.460
No.

36:00.560 --> 36:02.403
You got any special people?

36:22.400 --> 36:23.401
(WHISTLE BLOWING)

36:25.000 --> 36:26.445
WOMAN: Gully!

36:26.920 --> 36:29.446
Gully, this way! What are you doing?

36:31.040 --> 36:35.329
Gully, the team is going that way.
You need to stay with the team.

36:37.160 --> 36:38.525
I'm going to count to three.

36:39.120 --> 36:41.805
If not, it's five on the bench,
young man.

36:42.600 --> 36:44.011
One!

36:44.520 --> 36:46.124
Two!

36:46.400 --> 36:48.687
- (WHISTLE BLOWS)
- NANA: Hey.

36:49.280 --> 36:50.850
What's the problem?

36:51.120 --> 36:53.726
Excuse me, I'm talking to you.

36:54.480 --> 36:58.300
He's swimming. What difference does it make
if he swims there, he swims over there?

36:58.400 --> 36:59.900
Just let him swim, please.

37:00.000 --> 37:01.820
Ms. Ephron, the point of this class

37:01.920 --> 37:03.260
- is team swim.
- Okay, fine.

37:03.360 --> 37:06.180
He's swimming.
He's doing the best he can.

37:06.280 --> 37:10.046
All right, feel free to sign your son up
for guppy classes, then.

37:11.880 --> 37:15.327
Gully, out of the pool. Come on.
Ivan, you, too.

37:15.480 --> 37:16.860
Mom, no!

37:16.960 --> 37:18.644
NANA: Let's go. Now.

37:22.640 --> 37:25.405
Hurry up, Ivan. Let's get out of here.

37:27.800 --> 37:31.043
It's no fair.
I don't want to go because of Gully.

37:33.960 --> 37:35.246
Come here.

37:37.280 --> 37:39.123
You guys love each other, right?

37:41.000 --> 37:42.843
That's the most important thing.

37:43.680 --> 37:45.900
I would've done anything
to have a brother or sister.

37:46.000 --> 37:47.081
You know that?

37:48.800 --> 37:50.848
So you have to be there for each other.

37:51.960 --> 37:54.122
Always. Okay?

37:56.600 --> 37:58.204
Okay.

37:58.880 --> 38:00.405
Now say you love each other. Go on.

38:02.120 --> 38:05.044
I love you lots, big brother.

38:06.520 --> 38:07.726
(SIGHS)

38:09.520 --> 38:11.010
Lots.

38:18.520 --> 38:20.500
IKE: You shouldn't have
taken him out of that class.

38:20.600 --> 38:21.840
(SNIFFS)

38:22.960 --> 38:24.100
He needs looking after.

38:24.200 --> 38:25.565
I took care of it, Ike.

38:26.560 --> 38:27.891
He's in another class.

38:28.800 --> 38:30.325
Yeah.

38:30.880 --> 38:32.564
But his feelings, Alana.

38:34.600 --> 38:36.841
- He never comes first.
- Yeah.

38:37.520 --> 38:39.020
Well...

38:39.120 --> 38:40.485
He doesn't need to.

38:41.680 --> 38:43.444
Do him good to learn that.

38:45.920 --> 38:47.410
Ivan's strong.

38:48.680 --> 38:50.250
He can handle it.

38:52.680 --> 38:54.603
You think you know everything.

38:56.800 --> 38:58.882
- He's just a boy.
- (WOOD CLATTERS)

39:25.120 --> 39:26.246
NANA: So?

39:28.760 --> 39:30.046
What?

39:31.080 --> 39:32.525
So what?

39:34.440 --> 39:36.761
So, were you able to get in touch
with that doctor?

39:37.640 --> 39:38.721
Oh...

39:39.840 --> 39:41.660
You know, that's, uh...

39:41.760 --> 39:43.205
That's Clara's cousin.

39:46.040 --> 39:47.326
Yeah.

39:49.800 --> 39:53.860
So, you know, it's obvious
he's not gonna want to help you.

39:53.960 --> 39:55.849
Why? Why is it obvious?

39:57.040 --> 39:58.690
Is it honestly that surprising?

40:03.040 --> 40:04.371
Yeah.

40:05.440 --> 40:06.805
Yeah, it is.

40:07.560 --> 40:09.050
He's a little boy, Hans.

40:09.960 --> 40:12.060
Just try putting yourself
in her shoes for a minute.

40:12.160 --> 40:13.740
I'd fucking love to.

40:13.840 --> 40:14.940
'Cause my biggest problem would be

40:15.040 --> 40:17.980
that my husband screws around,
not that my son is dying.

40:18.080 --> 40:19.740
Come on, get a grip.

40:19.840 --> 40:22.540
I know this is tough on you,
but you don't have to take it out on me.

40:22.640 --> 40:24.324
Do you know what? I'm not her problem.

40:24.440 --> 40:26.920
You're her fucking problem, not me.

40:28.800 --> 40:30.848
Sure as hell not Gully.

40:31.960 --> 40:33.371
Come on, Nana.

40:33.880 --> 40:36.420
You need to start looking at things
a little bit differently here,

40:36.520 --> 40:38.204
just for your son's sake.

40:41.040 --> 40:42.260
Differently?

40:42.360 --> 40:43.521
Yeah.

40:45.080 --> 40:46.411
How?

40:47.360 --> 40:49.100
For Gully's sake.

40:49.200 --> 40:50.929
Try accepting it.

40:53.280 --> 40:55.203
Come on. Calm down.

40:55.400 --> 40:56.900
- Let's talk about this later.
- I said I'm done.

40:57.000 --> 40:58.620
- Excuse me.
- You want to finish dressing

40:58.720 --> 40:59.900
- before you go out there?
- Excuse me.

41:00.000 --> 41:02.765
- People are gonna find out.
- Everyone fucking knows, asshole.

41:07.000 --> 41:08.161
Excuse me.

41:09.560 --> 41:11.050
I don't mean to be a bother.

41:11.520 --> 41:12.900
NANA: You should leave me alone.

41:13.000 --> 41:15.241
I'm just asking a minute of your time.

41:17.320 --> 41:20.085
I wanted to apologize
for what I did to your boy's bird.

41:21.720 --> 41:23.210
Okay. Why?

41:24.240 --> 41:25.446
Why?

41:26.440 --> 41:28.283
I shouldn't be here, I know.

41:29.200 --> 41:30.725
I got no other choice.

41:32.600 --> 41:34.340
We're not from around here.

41:34.440 --> 41:38.206
Look, I lost my job. I left everything
to follow the Architect.

41:38.840 --> 41:40.808
If there was more time, you know,

41:41.120 --> 41:43.964
we'd wait for his next act,
but we're out of it.

41:44.600 --> 41:47.171
He's willing to try it
just for Lincey, but...

41:48.040 --> 41:51.140
But what? Let him try.

41:51.240 --> 41:54.369
The boy's eye.
He told us it was you made it happen.

41:55.600 --> 41:59.180
You might not want to help me exactly,
and I respect that, but I couldn't not try.

41:59.280 --> 42:00.700
He doesn't know what he's talking about.

42:00.800 --> 42:04.282
He's a dirty, old, pathetic drunk.
You shouldn't follow him anywhere.

42:05.880 --> 42:07.450
Look, I don't understand.

42:10.000 --> 42:12.890
Why'd you go in the first place
if you don't believe?

42:18.800 --> 42:20.290
Good luck with your little boy.

42:22.840 --> 42:24.683
I hope you find the help you need.

42:29.760 --> 42:30.966
(ENGINE STARTING)

42:43.160 --> 42:46.004
(BREATHING SHAKILY) Why'd you tell
that man I could help him?

42:46.480 --> 42:48.562
Consider it an opportunity for revenge.

42:48.680 --> 42:50.444
I don't want revenge.

42:51.560 --> 42:53.140
Then tell him you won't do it.

42:53.240 --> 42:55.208
That's not the point.

42:55.440 --> 42:57.340
So, why not help him, then?

42:57.440 --> 42:58.601
Fuck you!

42:59.720 --> 43:01.290
Fuck you!

43:03.520 --> 43:06.683
If it's because it frightens you
to think it might be useless,

43:07.680 --> 43:08.727
that frightens him, too.

43:08.960 --> 43:10.166
(GRUNTS)

43:12.360 --> 43:13.850
No...

43:19.000 --> 43:21.048
What am I supposed to do?

43:22.440 --> 43:25.250
The same thing you do
with your little boy.

44:12.160 --> 44:13.810
(TIRES SCREECHING)

44:18.960 --> 44:20.610
(ENGINE TURNS OFF)

44:21.280 --> 44:23.328
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

44:25.520 --> 44:26.931
Hey.

44:29.240 --> 44:30.401
Hey, buddy!

44:36.920 --> 44:38.809
- Can you open this?
- (DOOR OPENING)

44:53.200 --> 44:54.260
(JANIA WHISPERS IN FRENCH)

44:54.360 --> 44:55.691
Come on.

44:58.800 --> 45:02.327
- MAN: Sorry, sir, uh, there has been a truck...
- (MACHINE WHIRRING)

45:17.480 --> 45:18.940
MAN: No, if there was another way,

45:19.040 --> 45:21.700
I wouldn't be escorting vehicles
over 100 miles of frozen lake.

45:21.800 --> 45:24.201
Sir, I don't have two days,
I have to go through today.

45:24.320 --> 45:27.460
Well, unless you're planning on walking
clear across the lake,

45:27.560 --> 45:29.847
you're gonna have to just go home
like everybody else.

45:31.720 --> 45:33.245
(WIND HOWLING)

46:10.520 --> 46:13.524
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

46:34.560 --> 46:35.700
(BELLS JINGLE)

46:35.800 --> 46:37.040
(FALCON SQUEAKS)

46:41.760 --> 46:43.842
(WIND HOWLING)

46:50.200 --> 46:51.406
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

46:53.480 --> 46:54.970
(ICE CREAKING)

47:21.400 --> 47:22.925
JANIA: Ivan?

47:24.560 --> 47:25.641
Uh...

47:26.280 --> 47:27.420
Ivan?

47:27.520 --> 47:29.220
IVAN: (SHAKILY) The ice is gonna break.

47:29.320 --> 47:30.380
JANIA: What?

47:30.480 --> 47:32.801
IVAN: I'm telling you, the ice
is gonna break. I can fucking hear it.

47:33.920 --> 47:35.649
I can see the crack.

47:36.280 --> 47:37.884
JANIA: It's not going to break!

47:38.000 --> 47:39.764
IVAN: Don't come near me.

47:40.040 --> 47:42.486
Ivan, you have to trust me now, okay?

47:44.400 --> 47:45.640
No, stay there.

47:45.800 --> 47:47.540
Please, please stop!

47:47.640 --> 47:49.020
Ivan, it's not going to break.

47:49.120 --> 47:51.020
Don't come near me, please!

47:51.120 --> 47:52.690
Look at my face.

47:53.200 --> 47:54.884
Look at me, look at me.

47:55.120 --> 47:56.610
Just look at me.

48:19.160 --> 48:20.650
Okay?

48:22.640 --> 48:24.005
Let's go.

48:30.280 --> 48:31.327
(WHISPERS) Sorry.

48:31.960 --> 48:33.246
It's fine.

48:41.280 --> 48:43.521
MALE OFFICER: We're almost there.
Pretty small town.

48:44.080 --> 48:45.605
I can probably find you
a rental in the morning.

48:49.000 --> 48:50.740
You know what, why don't you
guys stay at my place tonight?

48:50.840 --> 48:53.844
We'll get you some food, warm you up,

48:54.360 --> 48:55.521
and, uh, get you on the road
in the morning.

48:55.640 --> 48:57.563
- Sound good?
- Thank you.

48:59.040 --> 49:00.883
- It's great.
- IVAN: Thanks.

49:03.000 --> 49:05.128
IVAN: Sorry I haven't called before now.

49:05.680 --> 49:08.001
Uh, reception's being a little shitty.

49:08.160 --> 49:09.241
Um...

49:11.080 --> 49:12.445
Miss you guys.

49:13.560 --> 49:15.005
Adiós, amigos.

49:16.840 --> 49:19.540
OFFICER: If you want to make
a phone call, too, you can go right ahead.

49:19.640 --> 49:20.620
JANIA: Oh, no, thank you.

49:20.720 --> 49:22.980
- The cell towers are spotty out there.
- JANIA: Yeah.

49:23.080 --> 49:24.220
- Okay.
- So, what happened?

49:24.320 --> 49:27.780
So, he gets stuck out on the ice road.
Almost dies.

49:27.880 --> 49:30.300
Walks for miles, hours.

49:30.400 --> 49:33.940
Finally, he gets to the town,
and a family takes him in.

49:34.040 --> 49:36.486
Can you believe that?
Dying stranger. Anyway...

49:37.520 --> 49:38.660
(BOY LAUGHING)

49:38.760 --> 49:41.923
He's coming. He's coming.

49:44.360 --> 49:46.488
Get that little guy... Oh, no!

49:46.760 --> 49:48.444
- And that is the extent of my French.
- (CHUCKLES)

49:49.560 --> 49:50.980
Cheers.

49:51.080 --> 49:52.140
(IVAN YELLING INDISTINCTLY)

49:52.240 --> 49:54.300
He's awake! Oh, no! He's after me!

49:54.400 --> 49:58.300
- He's after me! He's after me. He's after me.
- (SQUEALS)

49:58.400 --> 49:59.380
Oh, no.

49:59.480 --> 50:00.641
- Quick, hide!
- JANIA: He's cute.

50:01.080 --> 50:02.605
Thank you.

50:03.280 --> 50:04.770
He's not always cute.

50:05.280 --> 50:06.770
But tonight he's cute.

50:09.400 --> 50:10.380
He's coming to get me.

50:10.480 --> 50:12.940
Listen, I'm using
my work truck all week,

50:13.040 --> 50:15.980
and we have a Jeep
that you guys are free to use.

50:16.080 --> 50:18.340
- Oh, thank you.
- Yeah?

50:18.440 --> 50:20.966
- I don't know how to say thanks.
- No.

50:21.080 --> 50:23.606
- Don't worry about it.
- Thank you.

50:24.560 --> 50:25.500
(KISSES)

50:25.600 --> 50:26.761
- Bye.
- OFFICER: What about me?

50:29.000 --> 50:31.162
Towels on the bed. Clean sheets.

50:32.320 --> 50:34.084
I'm not asking any questions.

50:35.000 --> 50:36.180
- I'm going to bed.
- (JANIA CHUCKLES)

50:36.280 --> 50:37.725
- Good night.
- Thank you.

50:40.800 --> 50:42.290
(JANIA GRUNTS)

50:48.120 --> 50:49.485
Sweet kid.

50:53.080 --> 50:55.606
- (KEYBOARD CLACKING)
- (DOOR OPENING)

51:22.320 --> 51:24.846
I've never seen
such beautiful destruction.

51:33.160 --> 51:34.366
(BELL JINGLES)

51:49.360 --> 51:51.567
NANA: You told the woman back
at the house where I could find you.

51:53.920 --> 51:55.490
She sent that for you.

52:00.760 --> 52:02.888
But you haven't come here
just to feed me, have you?

52:05.480 --> 52:07.403
We need some more
of these, just like that.

52:15.080 --> 52:16.730
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

52:24.440 --> 52:27.728
NEWMAN: (SINGING)
But she's gone and married a lighterman

52:27.880 --> 52:30.963
So it's time for me to go

52:33.280 --> 52:37.842
But I would have loved you so, my dear

52:38.920 --> 52:42.402
I would have loved you so

52:46.200 --> 52:49.660
Oh, a shake o' the foresheet

52:49.760 --> 52:52.140
Pays for all

52:52.240 --> 52:53.820
For an alehouse shot

52:53.920 --> 52:56.605
And a friend forgot

52:58.200 --> 52:59.900
And a sweetheart

53:00.000 --> 53:02.082
False or kind

53:03.640 --> 53:05.802
And I would

53:06.000 --> 53:08.420
Have loved you so

53:08.520 --> 53:11.091
My dear

53:13.960 --> 53:15.564
You have good hands.

53:18.120 --> 53:21.442
I used to sew all the hoods
for my husband's falcons.

53:22.960 --> 53:26.328
They say you're not a falconer
unless you know how to sew,

53:28.640 --> 53:30.847
but he used to have me
do it for him on the sly.

53:33.160 --> 53:35.367
People used to come
from all over to buy them.

53:36.480 --> 53:38.084
But he never told the truth.

53:39.120 --> 53:41.441
No one ever knew it was me
that made them.

53:42.600 --> 53:43.806
Can't say I blame him.

53:46.480 --> 53:48.528
I could get used
to having you build for me.

53:50.560 --> 53:52.369
On the sly.

53:55.800 --> 53:57.802
Would I have to marry you
for the privilege?

54:07.880 --> 54:10.580
- IKE: Okay. All right, ease up on the brake.
- (VEHICLE APPROACHING)

54:10.680 --> 54:13.580
Real easy, now. Real easy.

54:13.680 --> 54:16.331
That's good. Doing good.

54:17.360 --> 54:19.601
Okay, keep turning the wheel.

54:20.680 --> 54:21.841
Little more gas.

54:32.280 --> 54:33.700
(GULLY SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

54:33.800 --> 54:35.529
(NANA CHUCKLES)

54:38.960 --> 54:40.644
(HUMMING)

55:06.560 --> 55:07.766
(WHISPERS) Ivan.

55:32.520 --> 55:34.090
(CRYING)

55:36.520 --> 55:37.851
(SNIFFLES)

56:02.120 --> 56:03.645
I love you, Ivan.

56:07.800 --> 56:08.961
(DOOR OPENING)

56:09.720 --> 56:10.881
(DOOR CLOSING)

56:12.120 --> 56:13.565
(CRYING)

56:25.840 --> 56:27.410
(SONG PLAYING)

57:22.840 --> 57:24.420
(VEHICLE DOOR CLOSES)

57:24.520 --> 57:26.010
(WHISPERS) What do you think, huh?

57:30.000 --> 57:31.490
- What do you think?
- (SCREECHES SOFTLY)

57:32.240 --> 57:33.765
Hey.

57:39.200 --> 57:40.440
(SNIFFS)

57:45.720 --> 57:46.801
You ready?

57:47.840 --> 57:49.604
Hey, you ready?

57:50.760 --> 57:52.285
You ready?

57:53.360 --> 57:55.840
Okay. Okay.

57:57.360 --> 57:58.850
Okay.

58:00.720 --> 58:01.846
(BELLS JINGLING)

58:04.040 --> 58:05.405
(SIGHS)

58:12.720 --> 58:14.260
All right.

58:14.360 --> 58:15.930
Put your hand out like this.

58:19.120 --> 58:20.451
Hold it up.

58:25.920 --> 58:27.081
Okay.

58:31.320 --> 58:32.890
Put this here.

58:33.440 --> 58:35.329
All right, you hold it up. Hold it up.

58:36.320 --> 58:37.660
Okay.

58:37.760 --> 58:39.460
He's gonna come right there.

58:39.560 --> 58:41.005
Okay?

58:42.280 --> 58:43.691
Okay.

58:47.040 --> 58:48.121
(WHISTLES)

58:52.000 --> 58:53.001
- (BELL JINGLING)
- (JANIA GASPS)

58:54.960 --> 58:57.804
- (CHUCKLES)
- IVAN: That's it. That's it.

59:00.360 --> 59:01.691
Okay.

59:01.960 --> 59:03.325
Yeah.

59:04.600 --> 59:06.409
- Can I touch him?
- Yeah.

59:09.000 --> 59:10.580
JANIA: He's not afraid.

59:10.680 --> 59:12.808
- That's his happy face.
- (LAUGHS)

59:13.360 --> 59:14.964
He's happy with you.

59:17.240 --> 59:18.765
That's his happy face.

59:35.000 --> 59:36.650
JANIA: This is so beautiful.

59:53.920 --> 59:54.940
Move!

59:55.040 --> 59:56.740
I'm gonna be as quick
as I can, all right?

59:56.840 --> 59:58.569
(BAG ZIPPER CLOSES)

01:00:01.760 --> 01:00:02.886
- Hey.
- (KNOCKING ON WINDOW)

01:00:03.000 --> 01:00:04.809
If you need me, just honk.

01:00:11.280 --> 01:00:13.380
GULLY: Yay, we can... again.

01:00:13.480 --> 01:00:15.130
(MIMICS GUNSHOTS)

01:00:15.960 --> 01:00:18.566
Look out. Incoming. (MIMICS EXPLOSIONS)

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:31.446
(GULLY HUMMING)

01:00:43.200 --> 01:00:44.645
GULLY: Stop it!

01:00:45.040 --> 01:00:47.008
I'll tell Mom even more.

01:00:52.440 --> 01:00:53.660
I better go find her.

01:00:53.760 --> 01:00:56.240
We're not allowed to get out.

01:00:56.600 --> 01:00:58.682
I'm in charge. You're not.

01:01:22.160 --> 01:01:24.083
(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

01:01:28.440 --> 01:01:30.920
MAN: ...through her body.

01:01:35.760 --> 01:01:37.250
Thank you so much.

01:01:56.680 --> 01:01:58.489
(WHISPERS) Lean back. Are you ready?

01:02:12.800 --> 01:02:15.121
(PANTING)

01:02:30.360 --> 01:02:31.646
Move over.

01:02:34.680 --> 01:02:36.603
- (DOOR CLOSING)
- What about Mommy? Where is she?

01:02:37.160 --> 01:02:39.686
She told me to take you home.
She's gonna be a while.

01:02:40.640 --> 01:02:43.041
- (ENGINE STARTING)
- You don't know how to drive.

01:02:43.320 --> 01:02:45.322
Of course I do. Papa Ike taught me.

01:02:45.520 --> 01:02:47.090
Put your seat belt on.

01:03:04.960 --> 01:03:06.530
GULLY: I can't see anything.

01:03:08.560 --> 01:03:10.005
IVAN: There's a button for this.

01:03:11.280 --> 01:03:12.520
What's happening?

01:03:14.480 --> 01:03:15.561
Ivan!

01:03:33.600 --> 01:03:34.840
GULLY: Where are we?

01:03:38.240 --> 01:03:39.730
(ICE CRACKING)

01:03:43.120 --> 01:03:45.566
It's a lake! Get out! Hurry!

01:03:45.720 --> 01:03:46.926
Open the door! Just get out!

01:03:51.080 --> 01:03:52.411
It's stuck!

01:03:54.440 --> 01:03:56.204
- (GRUNTS)
- Ivan! Wait!

01:03:57.160 --> 01:03:58.400
We're going in!

01:03:58.520 --> 01:04:00.010
Open the window! Quickly!

01:04:01.360 --> 01:04:02.407
(GRUNTS)

01:04:05.480 --> 01:04:08.900
Go! Hurry! Go!

01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:10.081
Ivan!

01:04:10.520 --> 01:04:13.967
- Ivan!
- Hurry! Now! Go!

01:04:14.360 --> 01:04:16.522
- Ivan, I'm scared!
- Now! Go!

01:04:18.920 --> 01:04:19.967
(WATER SPLASHES)

01:04:24.960 --> 01:04:26.166
Gully?

01:04:26.400 --> 01:04:27.811
Gully!

01:04:29.120 --> 01:04:30.451
Gully?

01:04:32.320 --> 01:04:34.322
Where are you, Gully?

01:04:34.440 --> 01:04:36.647
Gully! Gully!

01:04:36.760 --> 01:04:38.762
Come on, Gully!

01:04:40.600 --> 01:04:42.011
Hey!

01:04:43.560 --> 01:04:45.289
Gully!

01:04:47.000 --> 01:04:48.365
(SPLASHES)

01:05:40.520 --> 01:05:41.851
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:05:42.640 --> 01:05:43.846
(GRUNTS)

01:06:00.200 --> 01:06:01.804
Where are they?

01:06:04.200 --> 01:06:05.804
Ivan!

01:06:07.200 --> 01:06:08.531
Ivan!

01:06:49.080 --> 01:06:51.242
May I offer you some coffee, some tea?

01:06:51.760 --> 01:06:53.250
- Uh, no.
- No?

01:06:55.120 --> 01:06:59.728
We thought you would be coming alone,
but we understand in your situation...

01:07:00.800 --> 01:07:03.340
I'm honestly surprised you made it.

01:07:03.440 --> 01:07:04.420
It's...

01:07:04.520 --> 01:07:07.126
A lot of people got stuck out there.

01:07:08.080 --> 01:07:09.411
So...

01:07:09.600 --> 01:07:10.620
Um... (CLEARS THROAT)

01:07:10.720 --> 01:07:13.405
- Everything should be here.
- Ah. Great.

01:07:14.200 --> 01:07:17.124
Some are in French.
I can translate if you need.

01:07:17.280 --> 01:07:18.300
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

01:07:18.400 --> 01:07:19.606
It won't be necessary.

01:07:21.280 --> 01:07:22.805
Single.

01:07:23.200 --> 01:07:27.171
Diagnosed in 2011.

01:07:28.120 --> 01:07:32.523
You stopped treatment 5 months ago.

01:07:33.520 --> 01:07:34.965
No kids.

01:07:37.240 --> 01:07:38.287
Wait, what is this?

01:07:40.880 --> 01:07:42.120
JANIA: Ivan.

01:07:45.360 --> 01:07:47.660
Ivan. Ivan, stop.

01:07:47.760 --> 01:07:52.084
I'm just asking your companion
some final questions about her illness.

01:07:56.120 --> 01:07:57.485
(FILE THUDS)

01:08:12.960 --> 01:08:13.940
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

01:08:14.040 --> 01:08:15.166
I am sorry.

01:08:19.520 --> 01:08:22.046
I don't know what to say.

01:08:22.720 --> 01:08:25.929
I don't know why he reacted like that.

01:08:27.560 --> 01:08:28.740
(SIGHS)

01:08:28.840 --> 01:08:31.491
I hope... I don't know.

01:08:32.040 --> 01:08:34.247
I don't know what to say.

01:08:35.319 --> 01:08:37.720
I don't know why...

01:08:37.960 --> 01:08:39.246
I am so sorry.

01:08:40.880 --> 01:08:43.531
I hope this doesn't change anything.

01:08:44.040 --> 01:08:45.041
Please.

01:08:45.359 --> 01:08:46.420
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

01:08:46.520 --> 01:08:47.885
You want Nana?

01:08:48.439 --> 01:08:49.566
Mmm.

01:08:50.319 --> 01:08:51.765
(CRYING)

01:08:52.960 --> 01:08:55.167
Don't worry my little girl.

01:08:57.840 --> 01:09:00.810
Don't worry. Be strong.

01:09:04.720 --> 01:09:06.961
I have some documents for you.

01:09:07.920 --> 01:09:10.729
- Sign the papers.
- Thank you.

01:09:11.080 --> 01:09:13.367
WOMAN: (IN ENGLISH)
Confidentiality agreement.

01:09:17.359 --> 01:09:18.500
Thank you.

01:09:18.600 --> 01:09:19.840
(SIGHS)

01:09:26.840 --> 01:09:28.540
IVAN: Give me the keys.

01:09:28.640 --> 01:09:29.700
Give me the keys. I need the keys.

01:09:29.800 --> 01:09:31.580
- What was that? What was that?
- What?

01:09:31.680 --> 01:09:34.001
She was this close to
not giving me the coordinates.

01:09:34.920 --> 01:09:38.140
She doesn't heal people.
You know that, right?

01:09:38.240 --> 01:09:40.100
No! I don't, and neither do you.

01:09:40.200 --> 01:09:41.580
Give me the keys.

01:09:41.680 --> 01:09:43.939
Jesus Christ, give me the fucking keys.

01:09:44.040 --> 01:09:45.420
JANIA: What's bothering you?

01:09:45.520 --> 01:09:48.460
What's bothering you, that I'm sick?
Or that I think your mother could cure me?

01:09:48.560 --> 01:09:50.005
No. That you lie.

01:09:50.319 --> 01:09:54.689
That you lie. That you're
a fucking phony, just like her.

01:09:55.520 --> 01:09:57.090
Are you even a journalist?

01:09:58.520 --> 01:09:59.965
Fuck.

01:10:01.960 --> 01:10:03.644
I don't owe you, Ivan.

01:10:04.600 --> 01:10:06.250
Ivan, I don't.

01:10:07.520 --> 01:10:09.522
You don't get to know everything.

01:10:10.800 --> 01:10:12.140
What are you doing?

01:10:12.240 --> 01:10:13.526
(PANTING)

01:10:15.480 --> 01:10:17.220
You are just as delusional

01:10:17.320 --> 01:10:21.211
as the rest of her fucking groupies.

01:10:22.640 --> 01:10:24.847
So, go. Go.

01:10:25.120 --> 01:10:27.088
- Don't say that to me.
- Just go.

01:10:27.200 --> 01:10:30.329
Don't say that to me.
You don't say that to me.

01:10:31.160 --> 01:10:34.660
I left everything behind. Everything.

01:10:34.760 --> 01:10:36.540
And at least I have the guts
to do what I need to do.

01:10:36.640 --> 01:10:39.371
I'm not like you, hiding in my cage.
Fuck you!

01:10:45.840 --> 01:10:47.080
(SNIFFS)

01:10:47.720 --> 01:10:49.245
(ENGINE STARTS)

01:11:22.880 --> 01:11:25.565
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:11:32.880 --> 01:11:34.405
(FALCON SCREECHING)

01:13:07.960 --> 01:13:09.485
(DOOR CREAKING)

01:13:16.880 --> 01:13:18.245
(SNIFFLES)

01:13:36.760 --> 01:13:38.091
(SNIFFLES)

01:14:00.440 --> 01:14:01.726
(WHISPERS SHAKILY) Why?

01:14:15.720 --> 01:14:17.245
Why? (CRYING)

01:14:21.360 --> 01:14:22.964
Look at me!

01:14:23.760 --> 01:14:25.205
Look at me.

01:14:28.400 --> 01:14:29.686
Why?

01:14:30.280 --> 01:14:31.500
So what!

01:14:31.600 --> 01:14:34.410
He was just gonna die anyway!

01:14:36.360 --> 01:14:37.566
(YELLS)

01:14:45.800 --> 01:14:47.370
(SOFTLY) He wasn't.

01:14:48.280 --> 01:14:49.566
He wasn't.

01:15:07.120 --> 01:15:08.121
(DOOR CLOSING)

01:15:27.600 --> 01:15:29.090
Why don't you eat something?

01:15:41.760 --> 01:15:43.444
He hasn't said a word in weeks.

01:15:51.160 --> 01:15:54.130
I know you never listen much
to what I got to say, but...

01:15:57.400 --> 01:15:59.050
This time, I'm begging you.

01:16:02.240 --> 01:16:03.890
For Gully.

01:16:04.480 --> 01:16:05.925
Don't, Ike.

01:16:10.800 --> 01:16:12.165
Think it through.

01:16:15.160 --> 01:16:16.491
What about Ivan?

01:16:19.600 --> 01:16:21.170
(CLICKS TONGUE)

01:16:29.760 --> 01:16:32.420
We'll both have to find a way
to give meaning to all of it.

01:16:32.520 --> 01:16:33.760
IKE: Hmm.

01:16:35.640 --> 01:16:37.369
Well, explain that to him.

01:16:47.760 --> 01:16:49.000
(SIGHS)

01:16:55.240 --> 01:16:56.571
(SNIFFLES)

01:16:59.920 --> 01:17:01.570
NANA: Just gonna be for a little while.

01:17:03.400 --> 01:17:05.641
And you'll be staying with your grandpa.

01:17:07.800 --> 01:17:09.325
You like staying with him.

01:17:09.920 --> 01:17:11.206
Don't you?

01:17:13.440 --> 01:17:16.171
Now he's gonna be mad at me, too.

01:17:18.720 --> 01:17:20.370
Why is he gonna be mad?

01:17:20.840 --> 01:17:24.049
My hawk caught it
right before I could stop him.

01:17:24.800 --> 01:17:27.201
NANA: Well, he's a hawk.

01:17:27.880 --> 01:17:28.927
He's born to hunt.

01:17:29.880 --> 01:17:31.140
But Papa Ike says...

01:17:31.240 --> 01:17:33.368
Doesn't matter what Papa Ike says.

01:17:35.400 --> 01:17:36.765
What do you say?

01:17:38.480 --> 01:17:40.767
That's all that matters, okay?

01:17:47.240 --> 01:17:48.401
Come on.

01:17:49.160 --> 01:17:51.162
Let's have a real good-bye.

01:17:53.600 --> 01:17:55.602
Give your mom a kiss, okay?

01:18:04.520 --> 01:18:06.522
Ivan, you're a strong boy.

01:18:07.920 --> 01:18:09.922
You've always fended for yourself.

01:18:16.920 --> 01:18:18.126
Well...

01:18:19.280 --> 01:18:20.620
If you don't want to say good-bye,

01:18:20.720 --> 01:18:22.961
you don't have to say good-bye,
but I'm still going.

01:18:26.000 --> 01:18:28.207
You know this isn't easy for me, either.

01:18:35.920 --> 01:18:37.126
(SIGHS)

01:18:38.320 --> 01:18:39.651
Mom?

01:18:40.880 --> 01:18:42.120
(GRUNTS)

01:18:46.560 --> 01:18:48.927
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

01:19:31.640 --> 01:19:34.530
MALE VOLUNTEER: You're gonna have to
leave that camera equipment with me.

01:19:35.280 --> 01:19:38.602
Uh, we'll be sure to return it
when you guys are ready to leave.

01:19:39.120 --> 01:19:40.940
- She's just working outside right now.
- JANIA: Okay.

01:19:41.040 --> 01:19:43.122
- I'll let her know you guys are here.
- JANIA: Okay.

01:19:44.120 --> 01:19:45.690
- IVAN: Thank you.
- Thanks.

01:20:07.560 --> 01:20:09.449
- You okay?
- Mmm-hmm.

01:20:36.360 --> 01:20:38.249
(INDISTINCT MURMURING)

01:20:39.720 --> 01:20:41.290
(WOMAN LAUGHING)

01:20:50.160 --> 01:20:52.049
NANA: You can just
leave that there, thank you.

01:20:54.440 --> 01:20:55.500
(SNIFFS)

01:20:55.600 --> 01:20:57.060
Hi.

01:20:57.160 --> 01:20:58.605
Hello.

01:20:58.800 --> 01:21:00.300
Thank you so much.

01:21:00.400 --> 01:21:02.607
Such an honor meeting you.

01:21:03.960 --> 01:21:07.180
So we thought maybe
you could sit over here.

01:21:07.280 --> 01:21:08.486
NANA: Okay.

01:21:09.320 --> 01:21:12.563
So, first, you were
rather strict about your image,

01:21:12.680 --> 01:21:16.048
going so far as to forbid
any public record of your acts.

01:21:17.120 --> 01:21:18.360
Why the change?

01:21:20.400 --> 01:21:21.970
Well, that hasn't changed.

01:21:22.280 --> 01:21:25.170
We don't record the acts,
'cause it would defeat the purpose.

01:21:26.160 --> 01:21:29.020
But that has nothing to do
with my image.

01:21:29.120 --> 01:21:31.380
If you'd like to know
why I've resisted being filmed,

01:21:31.480 --> 01:21:34.700
I'd say because I'm beside the point,

01:21:34.800 --> 01:21:37.900
and I have no interest
in creating a product.

01:21:38.000 --> 01:21:39.126
But, um,

01:21:40.120 --> 01:21:41.406
if I'm honest...

01:21:43.520 --> 01:21:45.045
Um...

01:21:45.560 --> 01:21:47.608
I had a real issue with my own image.

01:21:49.640 --> 01:21:51.005
It made me anxious.

01:21:53.000 --> 01:21:57.060
But now, I'm approaching
my own death, so...

01:21:57.160 --> 01:21:58.924
I need to learn to relinquish control.

01:22:03.840 --> 01:22:05.900
JANIA: Newman Loslein,

01:22:06.000 --> 01:22:08.420
who was your mentor and guide,

01:22:08.520 --> 01:22:10.420
instilled in you the idea

01:22:10.520 --> 01:22:12.980
of art and nature

01:22:13.080 --> 01:22:16.700
as a means of healing.

01:22:16.800 --> 01:22:19.580
And I'm assuming part of his teachings

01:22:19.680 --> 01:22:21.523
touch on love.

01:22:22.200 --> 01:22:25.409
Could you elaborate
a little bit on that?

01:22:29.360 --> 01:22:31.203
I'm not interested in elaborating.

01:22:32.880 --> 01:22:34.405
You're asking me to perform,

01:22:36.360 --> 01:22:41.446
like, pluck love out of the sky
and examine it for you.

01:22:41.560 --> 01:22:43.085
It's not what I do.

01:22:44.640 --> 01:22:46.051
If you have a question,

01:22:48.280 --> 01:22:49.725
I'll try to answer it with you.

01:22:52.560 --> 01:22:53.925
My apologies.

01:22:56.040 --> 01:22:57.883
NANA: You don't need to apologize.

01:22:58.680 --> 01:23:00.364
You're making assumptions.

01:23:05.040 --> 01:23:06.610
Why the structures?

01:23:07.360 --> 01:23:10.011
Why bother traveling to the infinite?

01:23:11.400 --> 01:23:12.970
For the sake of art?

01:23:13.240 --> 01:23:14.526
Can you come here?

01:23:16.640 --> 01:23:17.926
I need your finger.

01:23:26.360 --> 01:23:29.540
You know, the problem

01:23:29.640 --> 01:23:32.928
is the moment I begin to explain an act,

01:23:33.760 --> 01:23:35.922
I start claiming it with language.

01:23:38.320 --> 01:23:39.460
Hmm...

01:23:39.560 --> 01:23:43.565
We want to take this possessive stance
with everything, right?

01:23:45.080 --> 01:23:46.730
But it only weakens us,

01:23:47.120 --> 01:23:49.964
whereas our well-being
demands an acceptance

01:23:51.360 --> 01:23:52.930
of uncertainty.

01:23:56.080 --> 01:23:57.570
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

01:24:04.800 --> 01:24:06.802
I have a question.

01:24:16.320 --> 01:24:18.322
How could a mother abandon her son

01:24:19.800 --> 01:24:22.326
for something she can't even explain?

01:24:40.080 --> 01:24:41.660
NANA: Could you turn that off?

01:24:41.760 --> 01:24:44.001
- (NANA CLEARS THROAT)
- (BUTTON CLICKS)

01:25:11.760 --> 01:25:13.603
You want to say something to me?

01:25:15.880 --> 01:25:18.247
It's a little late for that,
don't you think?

01:25:19.680 --> 01:25:21.980
So you came here for the interview?

01:25:22.080 --> 01:25:25.801
Yeah. Yeah,
I just came here for the interview.

01:25:26.120 --> 01:25:29.203
We should continue.
What's your favorite color?

01:25:29.560 --> 01:25:30.846
What, um...

01:25:31.400 --> 01:25:32.640
(SIGHS)

01:25:33.360 --> 01:25:36.648
Yeah, what book had the greatest
influence on your work?

01:25:37.840 --> 01:25:39.580
How's life been?

01:25:39.680 --> 01:25:40.920
Ivan.

01:25:47.880 --> 01:25:49.060
(WHISPERS) Ivan.

01:25:49.160 --> 01:25:51.020
(VOICE BREAKING) Do not say my name.

01:25:51.120 --> 01:25:53.566
Do not say my name!

01:25:57.600 --> 01:26:00.100
I came here because I wanted
to see what would happen.

01:26:00.200 --> 01:26:01.804
Simple as that.

01:26:03.320 --> 01:26:06.005
Because I knew you wouldn't come to me.

01:26:07.680 --> 01:26:11.900
And I thought maybe you'd crumble
like one of your goddamn sculptures,

01:26:12.000 --> 01:26:14.606
but you're not that easy
to break, are you?

01:26:16.880 --> 01:26:19.645
You'll just pick up the pieces
and start all over again.

01:26:23.280 --> 01:26:25.282
Isn't that how life works?

01:26:26.560 --> 01:26:27.925
Is that how life works?

01:26:29.200 --> 01:26:31.931
- No! What am I?
- (OBJECTS CLATTER)

01:26:32.440 --> 01:26:33.930
What am I?

01:26:35.800 --> 01:26:40.220
I'm just the collateral damage
for all your life's good work.

01:26:40.320 --> 01:26:41.606
Me!

01:26:42.120 --> 01:26:44.202
Me, right here!

01:26:51.600 --> 01:26:52.931
(SNIFFLES)

01:27:01.000 --> 01:27:02.843
(SOBBING)

01:27:06.000 --> 01:27:07.684
I didn't want him to die.

01:27:10.320 --> 01:27:11.810
I didn't want him to die.

01:27:15.160 --> 01:27:17.049
I didn't want him to die.

01:27:20.480 --> 01:27:21.561
(WHISPERS) Ivan.

01:27:24.520 --> 01:27:26.329
Ivan, it was too much to bear.

01:27:31.000 --> 01:27:33.685
It was too much to bear, Ivan.

01:28:07.960 --> 01:28:09.291
(SNIFFLES)

01:28:25.040 --> 01:28:26.644
Will you give her this?

01:28:59.160 --> 01:29:00.810
If you'd like to open them.

